Usage: get_power [-help] [-attribute <string>] [-include_unit]
                 [-instances <string>] [-nets <string>] [-outfile <string>]
                 [-pg_net <string>] [-pins <string>] [-tcl_list]

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
-attribute <string>     # turn on power attributes to be reported
                        # (string, optional)
-include_unit           # define unit has to be reported or not
                        # (bool, optional)
-instances <string>     # instance list to get attributes (string, optional)
-nets <string>          # net list to get power attributes (string, optional)
-outfile <string>       # output file (string, optional)
-pg_net <string>        # rail Name, to get rail specific power attributes of
                        # instances (string, optional)
-pins <string>          # pin list to get power attributes (string, optional)
-tcl_list               # returns a tcl list of query objects and attributes
                        # (bool, optional)